cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for pedestrian attribute recognition in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel multi-task model based on neural networks and temporal attention strategy, which involves training and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also presents two new large-scale video datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval) categories. Finally, the paper involves attribute recognition, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
